The Code

No-one speaks of The Code. In fact, just by telling you, the secret Canadian hockey police could come and take me away in the middle of the night, so this is between you and me.

In a nutshell, The Code is the way for players to offset the fact that at most levels of the game, refereeing is pitiful. It’s not the referees’ fault mind you - there are 12 players on the ice at a given time and usually only one referee who can call penalties, so a lot gets missed.

So, when someone take a cheap shot that isn’t caught by the referee, The Code is invoked. The team sends out its “enforcer” who challenges the offender to a fight. If the challenge is accepted, they fight, they both go to the penalty box, and honour is served. If the challenge is not accepted, it’s accepted that you’re essentially dooming your team’s biggest stars to open season at the hands of the other team.

